    preGame:
      "GOOD EVENING, OSTERRA! Or should I say, good baking? This is Nok the Corrupter, coming to you live via the screams of the damned from the Sun-Baked Bowl! And folks, when we say 'Sun-Baked,' we aren't speaking metaphorically! We are out here in the Great Desert, where the heat is oppressive, the sand is getting into places sand has no business being, and the dehydration is setting in faster than a potion from Imra, the Master of Elixirs‚Äîseriously, pay your bar tab, you dusty wizard!\n\nTonight, we have a clash of titans, a duel in the dunes! In the visiting corner, hailing from the coast and sponsored by the questionable ethics of Cedar Hill, we have THE TORTELL PRIVATEERS! They look ready to pillage and plunder! I just watched Dib Tufts chug a raw egg, shell and all, right on the sidelines! That is the kind of calcium-rich, throat-shredding intensity I like to see! And on the home sands, representing the domain of my frenemy Geth the Gravelord, give it up for THE DESERT SPECTRES! I saw Steve‚Äîjust Steve‚Äîorganizing a betting pool before the match. I put five gold pieces on 'first blood drawn by a rusted spoon,' but Steve wouldn't take the action!\n\nIt's going to be hot, it's going to be gritty, and with luck, it's going to be incredibly painful! The heat waves are shimmering, the weapons are sharpened, and the Healers are already sweating! Grab a cold drink, because these players certainly can't! LET'S PLAY TROLLBALL!",
    postGame:
      "BY THE FLAMING PITS OF THE UNDERWORLD! What a game, folks! What a brutal, sweaty, sand-choked display of violence! The Tortell Privateers marched into the Great Desert and snatched a victory right out of the skeletal hands of the Desert Spectres, winning this grimy affair 1 to 0! It wasn't pretty, it wasn't clean, but by the Abyss, it was entertaining!\n\nThe action started fast and loose! Dib Tufts snagged the ball early for the Privateers, but the chaos erupted immediately. We saw fumbles, we saw scrambles, and we saw blood! Muscolo Jaehne tried to get things moving for the Spectres, but the field turned into a swirling vortex of pain. I haven't seen this many bodies hit the floor since the last time Artorias tried to host a 'peaceful' dinner party!\n\nLet's talk about the carnage in the first half! It was a revolving door of violence! Goldberg Tova and Heyes Iver knocked each other into oblivion simultaneously! Then Goldberg came back and did the *exact same thing* with Eileen Mikihisa! Double Knockouts everywhere! The Healers, Eugen Zacks and Verlee Dacia, were working overtime, probably wishing they had some of Elspeth Ortell's disintegration magic just to clear the pileups!\n\nAnd Kidder Starkey! Talk about a rampage! This Privateer was stabbing anything that moved! They took out Lovash Marius, they took out Angelita Darce, they took out Muscolo! Kidder was playing like they owed money to the Guild of the Black Sky! Absolute ferocious energy!\n\nBut folks, the heat... the heat does strange things to the mind. In perhaps the most hilarious moment of the match, Loralee Sunny of the Privateers, perhaps blinded by the sun or just confused by the blood loss, managed to KNOCK THEMSELVES OUT with their own War Scythe! That's right! Loralee Sunny fought Loralee Sunny, and Loralee Sunny won! Or lost! I don't know, but I haven't laughed that hard since I saw Sir Tanos try to read a map!\n\nDespite the self-inflicted wounds, the Privateers found the end zone right after halftime. Dib Tufts, powered by raw eggs and sheer grit, punched through the line! Fidellia Mozelle tried to stop them, but it was too late! TOUCHDOWN PRIVATEERS! That single point would prove to be the only thing that mattered on the scoreboard, but certainly not the only thing that mattered to the infirmary!\n\nThe second half was a mess of friendly fire and desperation. Lilithe Royce decided to follow Loralee's example of confusion and knocked out their own teammate, Castorina Gies! The Privateers were so bloodthirsty they ran out of enemies and started attacking each other! That is the kind of chaotic energy I expect from a team associated with Elspeth Ortell!\n\nThe Desert Spectres tried to mount a comeback. Fidellia Mozelle, bless their heart, made a valiant run. They dodged blocks, they weaved through the carnage, they looked destiny in the eye... and then they missed the shot! The ball fell short, landing in the 2-point zone with a thud that echoed the disappointment of Geth the Gravelord watching from his crypt!\n\nIn the final minutes, it was just a brawl. Castorina Gies was desperately trying to pass, Muscolo was slashing away with a Seax, and the sand was turning into red mud. When the dust settled, the Privateers stood tall‚Äîwell, the ones who weren't unconscious stood tall.\n\nSo there you have it! The Tortell Privateers brave the heat, the sandstorms, and their own incompetence to take down the Desert Spectres 1-0! Geth, you might want to have a word with your squad; they let a bunch of egg-chugging pirates beat them in their own backyard! This is Nok the Corrupter, signing off! Go bandage your wounds, Osterra!",
