    preGame:
      "üéôÔ∏è **GOOD EVENING, SPORTS FANS!** Can you smell that? No, not the rotting corpse of a failed adventurer‚Äîit‚Äôs the sweet, sulfurous scent of **TUESDAY NIGHT TROLLBALL!** We are LIVE from the most beautiful disaster in all of Osterra, **The Sinking Field** in Ebon Gate! The mud is thick, the fumes are toxic, and the sinkholes are hungry! Just the way we like it! A perfect night for violence!\n\nTonight, my personal favorites, the hometown heroes of horror, **The Ebon Gate Corruptors**, are looking to stomp the visiting **The Greenwatch** right into the muck! I was peeking in the locker room and saw **Napoleon Anzovin** thanking his armor‚Äîsmart lad, because out here, cold steel is your only friend! And look at **As Utter**, insisting on being the last one out of the tunnel. That's the kind of drama I love!\n\nOn the other side, we have The Greenwatch. Ugh. They‚Äôre backed by those goody-two-shoes **Wardens**. I bet **Sir Randy** is watching from the bushes with his \"fancy bow,\" crying because no one is using ranged weapons! I saw their player, **Madea Mensch**, literally *tying his bootlaces together* during warmups. Is that a tactic? Is it a death wish? Who cares, as long as he bleeds! And **Troy Jorgan** is down there talking to the Trollball... asking it for advice! Lunatics, the lot of 'em! But they're 0-0, just like us, so anything can happen! Grab your popcorn and your antidotes, folks‚ÄîIT'S TIME FOR TROLLBALL! üëπüèà",
    postGame:
      "Well, folks, I‚Äôm not gonna lie to you, my heart is black and broken, but my bloodlust is somewhat satisfied! The final whistle has blown, and the scoreboard tells a tragic tale: **The Greenwatch 4, The Ebon Gate Corruptors 0**. A shutout! In our own swamp! It‚Äôs an absolute travesty, but don‚Äôt let that big fat zero fool you‚Äîthe violence out there was exquisite! üí•\n\nThe game started with a bang! Despite the tied shoelaces, **Madea Mensch** managed to scoop up the ball and fire a shot from Center Field for a quick **2 points**! A disgusting display of competence right out of the gate! But then, the real fun began. **Drona Jacklin** decided to introduce **Napoleon Anzovin** to the floor with a Kriegsmesser! BAM! And then? Chaos! **Troy Jorgan** and **Ahasuerus An** traded blows until *both* of them were knocked out cold! A double knockout! That‚Äôs the kind of hustle I like to see!\n\nThe mud at the Sinking Field claimed its victims today. We saw **Goldenberg Rimola** slipping through tackles like a greased pig, while our boys struggled to find their footing. But the violence kept coming! **Salahi Bushey** and **Ellette Paz** decided to skip the game and just murder each other, resulting in *another* double knockout! And then **Rese Halpern** and **Simsar Carrelli** did the exact same thing! The Healers, **Nariko Javed** and **Terle Chenay**, were working harder than a necromancer at a plague festival keeping these bodies moving!\n\nIn the second half, **Napoleon Anzovin** woke up on the wrong side of the dirt and went on a rampage, smashing **Troy Jorgan** with that massive Kirkhammer! CRUNCH! But the Corruptors just couldn't hold onto the rock. We saw some confusing plays‚Äîat one point **Olnek Vizzone** seemed to throw the ball directly to **Nobe Haukom** of the Greenwatch! Was that a pass? A bribe? A betrayal?! \n\nWhatever it was, it let **Verne Methuselah** set up for another shot, drilling it from Center Field for another **2 points**, sealing the doom of my beloved Corruptors. The game ended in a sloppy mess of fumbles, with **Ahasuerus An** and **Simsar Carrelli** dropping the ball more often than **Governor-King Zenku** drops his public approval rating!\n\nI blame the **Wardens** for this. This reeks of **Falric's** influence‚Äîhe probably bribed the mud to be less sticky for the visitors! Or maybe **Levania** dazzled my boys with something shiny from the sidelines! And don't think I didn't see **Cinnemon** in the stands, probably spreading \"literacy\" and distracting our players with big words! Disgusting!\n\nSo, the Greenwatch takes the win, but the Corruptors take the moral victory of inflicting severe blunt force trauma. And really, isn't that what life is all about? (No? It's about winning? Shut up!) Tune in next week, folks! This is **Nok the Corrupter**, signing off! Don't get disintegratred! üéôÔ∏èüíÄ",
