    preGame:
      '# üéôÔ∏è WELCOME TO THE SLAUGHTER!\n\nGood evening, sports fans, gore-hounds, and denizens of the dark! Nok the Corrupter here, broadcasting LIVE on the aether-waves for another bone-crunching edition of **TUESDAY NIGHT TROLLBALL!** ü©∏\n\nWe are coming to you from the wonderfully unstable **Unruly Yard** in New Monteforte! Folks, let me tell you, the scaffolding here looks like it was built by a drunken giant on a unicycle, and the crowd is already throwing rotten fruit at the officials! It is absolutely BEAUTIFUL! The air smells of ozone, sweat, and impending medical bills! üèüÔ∏è\n\nTonight, we have a clash of ideologies! In the away dugout, counting their coins and checking their life insurance policies, it\'s **The New Prosperity Profits**! They represent the Guild of the Black Sky. You know the type‚Äîled by Chairman Brennen Farno. I hear that man is a "money priest" and a kissless virgin. Hah! Maybe if he spent less time praying to gold and more time watching violence, he\'d have some fun! üí∞\n\nAnd facing them, the home team, the rebels without a clue, **The New Monteforte Chaos Creatures**! These guys are backed by the White Ravens. You know, Dame Terra Monteforte? The "Dirt Wizard"? She kidnaps prophets for fun! I respect the kidnapping, but the dirt magic? Wash your hands, lady! üßô‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è\n\nüëÄ **LOCKER ROOM SCOOPS:**\nI was peeking in the tunnels during warm-ups, and folks, the rituals are getting weird!\n\n*   **Pulchi Benyamin** of the Profits was seen staring blankly into space while eating a whole dandelion! Stem, flower, dirt, and all! That is fiber, folks!\n*   But the winner of the "Iron Stomach" award goes to the Chaos Creatures\' healer, **Lian Denton**. They were slamming back a shot of **HOT GRAVY** from a dented tin cup! Now THAT is how you prepare to stitch severed limbs back together! ü•£\n\nSo grab your popcorn, hide your valuables, and pray for carnage! The whistle is about to blow!',
    postGame:
      "# üèÅ POST-GAME WRAP-UP: PROFIT MARGINS AND BROKEN BONES!\n\n**FINAL SCORE:**\n**The New Prosperity Profits: 6**\n**The New Monteforte Chaos Creatures: 0**\n\nHot diggity damn! What a night at the Unruly Yard! We promised you violence, we promised you chaos, and we got a SHUTOUT! The Profits came into the rebel's house, kicked over the furniture, and stole the silverware! üßπ\n\n**THE FIRST HALF: TEDRIC'S TARGET PRACTICE**\nThe game started with **Gabriele Klehm** picking up the leather, looking to make a statement for Monteforte. But the only statement made was \"OUCH!\" The field immediately turned into a mosh pit! We saw a beautiful double-knockout early on‚Äî**Boleslaw Heathcote** and **Placido Kora** just deleted each other from existence simultaneously! POOF! Gone! That is the kind of efficiency I like to see! üí•\n\nBut the star of the first half was undoubtedly **Aufmann Tedric**. While everyone else was trying to murder each other, Tedric remembered there's actually a ball involved! After a block, Tedric grabbed the rock, looked up, and BAM! 2 points from Center Field! üéØ\n\nThe violence kept escalating! **Yoshi Cathy** and **Tucker Hett** traded blows in a spear-vs-billhook duel that ended with BOTH of them staring at the sky! But the Profits kept their eyes on the prize. Tedric, slippery as a greased eel, ran the ball all the way to Home Field and fired another shot! **4-0 Profits!**\n\n**THE HEALER OLYMPICS**\nI have to give a shoutout to **Lian Denton**, the Chaos Creatures' gravy-drinking healer. They were working overtime! Reviving Alben, Placido, Boleslaw (wait, Boleslaw is on the other team? Chaos indeed!), keeping the roster alive. But you can't heal a scoreboard, folks! üöë\n\nJust before the half, **Faina Hendrix** decided to join the party. While Lian was busy stitching people up, Faina launched a rocket from Center Field! Another 2 points! The Profits went into the locker room up **6-0**, leaving the Monteforte crowd stunned and rioting slightly less than usual.\n\n**THE SECOND HALF: A WALL OF PAIN**\nThe second half was a defensive clinic... or a massacre, depending on how you look at it. **Alben Diantha** tried to get something going for the Creatures, but **Gladdie Farika** said \"NOPE\" and blocked that run like a tax audit! üõë\n\n**Tucker Hett** of the Creatures woke up and chose violence, absolutely levelling Faina Hendrix with that Billhook. CRUNCH! Then Tucker took out Milman Galvan too! Tucker was playing Whac-A-Mole out there, but unfortunately, KOs don't put points on the board! You gotta respect the bloodlust, though. ü©∏\n\n**THE FINAL DESPERATION**\nLate in the game, it looked like the Profits might score again with **Boleslaw Heathcote**, but **Raouf Dragone** managed to steal possession! Raouf took off like a scalded cat! They ran to Away Field! They ran to the Away 2-Point zone! The crowd was screaming! Could they avoid the shutout? üèÉüí®\n\nNOPE! Time ran out with Raouf holding the bag! The Profits take the win, 6-0!\n\n**NOK'S FINAL THOUGHT**\nA tough night for the White Ravens and their scruffy rebels. Maybe if **Colm** wasn't so busy being the \"most cursed man in Osterra,\" he could have cursed the opponent's goalpost! And as for the Guild of the Black Sky? **Brennen Farno** is probably rolling around in a pile of gold right now. Disgusting. But hey, they brought the pain and they brought the points!\n\nThis is Nok the Corrupter, reminding you: It doesn't matter if you win or lose, as long as someone leaves on a stretcher! Goodnight, Osterra! üòà",
