    preGame:
      "GOOD EVENING, sports fans, and welcome to another ELECTRIFYING Tuesday Night Trollball broadcast! Nok the Corrupter here, broadcasting live to you from the ever-shifting, ever-dangerous Fletchings Field! \n\nTonight, we have a clash of titans, a meeting of monsters, a delightful dance of death! In the away corner, slithering out of the swamp with a distinct smell of wet moss and bad decisions, we have **The Zmeigorod Snessengers**! üêç I was watching them warm up, folks, and let me tell you, they are ready for violence. I saw Delija Dowling crack a raw egg into his mouth‚Äîshell and all! Crunch, crunch, gulp! That is the kind of calcium-rich insanity I look for in a killer! And their healer, Waldon Tadeo? They were vigorously rubbing a foul-smelling mushroom on their elbows. If that doesn't cure a severed limb, I don't know what will!\n\nAnd facing them, the home team, the defenders of the woods, **Oak & Onslaught**! üå≥‚öîÔ∏è Now, these folks are under the protection of the Wardens, specifically that fancy-pants Sir Randy. I bet Randy is too busy polishing his boots to watch, but his team is looking... confused? I see Wynnie Faina wearing his boots on the wrong feet! Is it a tactical genius move to confuse the enemy? Is it a severe concussion from last week? Who cares! It‚Äôs TROLLBALL! The terrain is shifting, the weapons are sharpened, and the crowd is baying for blood! Let's get down to the field and watch the carnage unfold!",
    postGame:
      'HOLY HELLS, folks! What a spectacle! What a display of beautiful, unadulterated VIOLENCE! ü©∏ If you missed this one, you missed a classic defensive struggle that exploded into a second-half shootout! The final score, after a nail-biting finish, stands with the home team taking the glory: **Oak & Onslaught 5, The Zmeigorod Snessengers 4**! Let\'s break down the brutality, shall we?\n\nThe first half was a masterclass in "How to Hurt People" but a disaster in "How to Score Points." Arni Griffith started things off for the Snessengers, giving the ball a heroic backstory, but then immediately missed a shot from Center Field! Just shameful! But the violence? Oh, it was exquisite. We saw Kleinstein MacGregor and Wynnie Faina trade blows in a beautiful synchronized double-knockout! One moment they were standing, the next? Both staring at the sky! üòµüí´\n\nThe clumsiness continued, folks! Millham Evangeline picked up the leather, missed a shot. Teria Ravo picked up the leather, missed a shot. It was like they were allergic to the goal! But the healers‚ÄîAhron Latashia and Waldon Tadeo‚Äîwere the MVPs of the first half, practically running a revolving door for the infirmary. \n\nWe saw another magnificent double-down when Avaria Revell and Symer Crissy clashed in the midfield. Bastard Sword met Pollaxe, and GRAVITY won! Both players hit the dirt, unconscious before they hit the ground. The first half ended 0-0, a scoreless draw that would make a pacifist weep with joy, but left us demons hungry for more!\n\nBUT THEN! The Halftime whistle blew, the cobwebs were cleared, and the offenses woke up! Ema Ulrick, fresh out of the medical tent, grabbed that Trollhead and launched a rocket from Home Field! BOOM! üí• 2 Points for Oak & Onslaught! The deadlock was broken!\n\nThe home team smelled blood! Wynnie Faina, boots still on the wrong feet, somehow managed to find his balance and fired another shot from Center Field! Another 2 points! Suddenly, it was 4-0, and the Snessengers looked like they were sinking back into their swamp!\n\nDon\'t count out the Snakes though! Dare Wynnie, with mud stripes painted on their face, grabbed the loose ball and fired back! A 2-point shot for Zmeigorod! The crowd went wild! The score tightened to 4-2, and the tension was thicker than the air in the Demon Prison!\n\nThen came the play of the game! Evalyn Pierrepont tried to run the ball for the Snessengers, but **Millham Evangeline** said "ABSOLUTELY NOT!" Millham blocked the run, stole the ball, and literally ran it into the goal for a Touchdown! üèÉüí® That put Oak up 5-2, and despite Rose Kluge\'s best efforts to stop it, the damage was done.\n\nThe Zmeigorod Snessengers had one last gasp in them. Gere Cordelie, wearing those nasty Spiked Gauntlets, launched a desperation shot from Center Field and... IT WAS GOOD! 2 more points! The score was 5-4!\n\nBut it was too little, too late! Delija Dowling grabbed the ball in the dying seconds, but time ran out on the Snessengers. Oak & Onslaught takes the victory!\n\nI have to say, for a team sponsored by the Wardens, Oak & Onslaught actually showed some spine today! Usually, Sir Randy is too busy looking in a mirror to teach his troops how to fight, and Falric is too busy losing money to buy decent armor, but today? Today they fought like demons! A glorious day for sports, a terrible day for the healers\' backs! Until next time, this is Nok the Corrupter signing off! STAY VIOLENT, OSTERRA! üòàüéôÔ∏è',
