    preGame:
      "Helloooooo Trollball fanatics, and welcome back to Tuesday Night Trollball! This is your favorite fiend, Nok the Corrupter, coming to you live from the ethereal airwaves! We have a real scorcher for you tonight, folks, a battle that‚Äôs going to make the very ground shake! In one corner, hailing from the sweltering Sun-Baked Bowl, we have The Desert Spectres! And in the other, crawling from the sulfurous stink of the Su'akour Ruins, it‚Äôs The Brimstone Fire Eaters!\n\nNow, these aren't your clean-cut, goody-two-shoes adventurers from Eponore, oh no! These are warriors, titans of the turf! The Spectres are getting ready by engaging in some truly inspired rituals. I'm seeing Angelita Darce out there shaving exactly one half of his mustache for the game‚Äîthat‚Äôs the kind of dedication that wins championships, my friends! And their healer, Verlee Dacia, is sweetening the deal by eating a piece of honeycomb. Let's hope that victory tastes just as sweet!\n\nBut don't you count out the home team! The Brimstone Fire Eaters live and breathe this gritty game! Just look at Glassman Solley, forgoing soap and water to wash their hands with the very dirt of the arena! And Bollinger Susette is warming up by having a teammate punch him square in the shoulder! You won't see Sir Artorias doing *that* before a big battle, I can tell you!\n\nThe air here is thick with anticipation and, in Brimstone's case, noxious fumes! The stage is set for a symphony of shattered bones and spectacular scores! Who will emerge from the dust and smoke victorious? We're about to find out! So grab your grog, place your bets with anyone *but* Yarp, and get ready for the most beautiful violence in all of Osterra! It's Trollball time!",
    postGame:
      "AND THAT'S THE GAME, FOLKS! What a spectacle! What a showdown! The Brimstone Fire Eaters have doused the desert flames, taking the win with a final score of 3 to 1! An absolutely electrifying performance here in the Su'akour Bowl!\n\nThe action started fast and furious right from the get-go! The ball was barely in play before Oona Jane of the Fire Eaters decided Lovash Marius had seen enough of the field for a while, sending them to the dirt with a mighty swing of their cudgel! That's how you set the tone, my friends!\n\nThe Desert Spectres tried to answer back, with Huesman Ring launching a prayer from center field, but it fell short. The ball then became a hot potato in the Fire Eaters' zone, a beautiful, chaotic scramble of fumbles, blocks, and stolen possessions. This is the heart of Trollball, a glorious mess that no battlefield commander could ever choreograph!\n\nBut the Spectres weren't just going to roll over! Heyes Iver brought out the big chopper, knocking Campball Fink out of the game with a Woodsman's Axe! In the ensuing chaos, Fidellia Mozelle scooped up the troll head and barrelled past the opposition for the first score of the night! A touchdown for the Spectres!\n\nAt halftime, the score was a nail-biting 1-0 in favor of the visitors. Both teams retreated to lick their wounds, and the healers, bless their souls, worked overtime to get everyone back on their feet for the second round of glorious brutality.\n\nAnd what a second half it was! The Brimstone Fire Eaters came out breathing, well, fire! Lowson Hersh put the team on their back, grabbing the ball and starting a determined march up the field.\n\nThe crunching tackles came thick and fast! We had a spectacular double knockout as Huesman Ring and Wylde Jutta traded blows and sent each other packing! You see that, Dame Terra? That's how you move the earth! A truly inspiring moment of mutual destruction!\n\nUndeterred by the carnage, Lowson Hersh continued their advance and, finding an opening, launched a perfect shot from the away field! It sailed through the goal for TWO BIG POINTS! The Fire Eaters took the lead, and the hometown crowd went absolutely wild!\n\nThe rest of the match was a blur of beautiful violence! We had more double KOs than a tavern brawl on payday! Bahr Ethelstan and Oona Jane took each other out! Muscolo Jaehne and Bollinger Susette followed suit! Then Steve and Selimah Tully decided to join the party! The healers were earning their pay tonight, folks! It was a meat grinder out there, the kind of recycling even Cyfnerth would approve of!\n\nAnd through it all, who emerged from the pile of bodies with the ball? None other than the hero of the half, Lowson Hersh! They dodged one last defender and plunged into the end zone for another score, sealing the victory for the Brimstone Fire Eaters! What a performance! An absolute masterclass in Trollball tenacity!\n\nSo let the record show, here on this glorious Tuesday night, The Brimstone Fire Eaters stand tall with a 3-to-1 victory over the Desert Spectres! A game full of grit, guts, and glorious, glorious violence! This is Nok the Corrupter, signing off! See you next time, you beautiful brutes!",
