    preGame:
      "Helloooooo sports fans, and welcome to another glorious Tuesday Night Trollball! This is your favorite host, Nok the Corrupter, coming to you live from the absolutely blinding Glowstone Terrace here in Confluence! My eyes! This place is certainly... polished. A far cry from the good, honest muck of the Ebon Gate pits, but the action promises to be just as dirty!\n\nTonight, we have a real treat for you as the hometown heroes, The Confluence Captains, take on the visiting New Ravenfall Commanders! The air is electric, the mountain wind is howling, and the market crowd down below is making a terrific racket! The Captains are looking... interesting in their warm-ups. Ladew Evelina is chugging raw eggs, shell and all! Now that's how you prepare for battle! Meanwhile, O'Conner Maighdlin is speaking only in rhymes, which I'm sure is just delightful for his teammates.\n\nThe visiting Commanders don't look like they're here for a poetry slam, folks! I see Theis Loredo and Pirozzo Opal sharing a bit of fermented fish‚Äîa bold move that's sure to keep defenders at a distance! And you have to love the sheer power of Jozef Pepe's pre-game ritual: a belching contest! That's the kind of team-building you just don't see from those stuffy Guild types like Chairman Farno. This promises to be a clash of styles, a battle of brute force against... well, slightly different brute force! It's going to be a beautiful, beautiful mess! Don't you dare touch that dial!",
    postGame:
      "WHAT A GAME, FOLKS! WHAT A FINISH! When the dust settled and the last body hit the gleaming stone of this ridiculous pitch, your New Ravenfall Commanders walk away with the victory, shutting out the hometown Captains TWO to NOTHING!\n\nA scoreless first half had us all wondering if these two teams were just going to dance around all night, but boy, did they prove old Nok wrong! It was a real defensive slobberknocker in that first half. We saw players on both sides taken out in spectacular fashion! Fleme Alis and Vonni Geoff went down together in a beautiful symphony of violence right at the start! Not to be outdone, Behl Berstine and Croteau Osmo decided to take a mutual trip to the healers' tent as well!\n\nThe ball was like a greased goblin out there, slipping through fingers and fumbling on the slick glowstone. Both teams had their chances, with Rhett Gavrilla and Carnahan Laud letting potential scoring shots fall short. It was a grinder, a real testament to the defensive might of these squads.\n\nThen came the second half, and everything changed! The whistle blew, and Dusa Curson of the Commanders came out with fire in her eyes! She scooped up the Trollball and, after a beautiful knockout from her teammate Estes Adrian, she made a break for it!\n\nShe weaved through the chaos, dodging would-be tacklers and ignoring the fresh carnage as Fleme Alis and Carnahan Laud decided to knock each other out of the game for a second time! With a mighty heave, Dusa Curson launched the Trollball from the 2-point zone... AND IT'S GOOD! A magnificent shot that put the Commanders on the board, 2-0!\n\nThat, my friends, is when the game truly descended into the glorious mayhem we all crave! The Confluence Captains, desperate to score, started throwing bodies around with reckless abandon. And the Commanders were more than happy to answer in kind!\n\nIt was a cascade of pure, unadulterated Trollball! Ladew Evelina knocked out Pirozzo Opal! Vonni Geoff and Estes Adrian took each other out! Behl Berstine laid out Jessalin Zobias! Deach Sharlene flattened Croteau Osmo!\n\nFleme Alis, having returned from his nap, decided he wasn't done and proceeded to knock out Stephan Lisk AND Richia Pazit! What a performance from that young man! The field was littered with bodies, and the healers were working overtime!\n\nIn the final moments, the Captains' star player, Ladew Evelina, made one last desperate push. She had the ball, she had a path, but she was met by a wall of granite named Theis Loredo! The block was perfect, the ball came loose, and that was all she wrote!\n\nA hard-fought, bone-crunching victory for The New Ravenfall Commanders! I'm sure their patron, Sir Tanos, is smiling somewhere. As for the Captains, well, maybe their Guild chairmen should spend less time admiring doors and more time teaching their players how to hold onto a ball! What a night! This is Nok the Corrupter, signing off!",
