    preGame:
      "Helloooooo Trollball fanatics, and welcome to another spectacular edition of **Tuesday Night Trollball**! This is your favorite demonic announcer, Nok the Corrupter, coming to you live from the most painfully pristine stadium in all of Osterra, The Aegis Field! üèüÔ∏è Yes, folks, we're deep in Haven territory, where the grass is a little too green and the air is a little too clean for my liking. But don't you worry, because we've got a matchup tonight that's guaranteed to stain this 'Hallowed Ground' with a bit of good, honest brutality!\n\nIn the home corner, we have the ever-pious, the ever-shining, **The Haven Lights**! üòá I've heard their pre-game rituals involve things like drinking lukewarm water and whispering their fears to the Trollball itself. It's a novel strategy, I'll give them that. Perhaps they're hoping to bore the opposition into submission! Let's see if their prayers to the Twin Lights will be enough to protect them from what's coming.\n\nAnd what's coming, you ask? Why, it's the challengers from the deep woods, the hard-hitting, the awe-inspiring **Wyrmwood Stronghammers**! üî® Now this is a team that knows how to get ready for a game! While the Lights are drawing diagrams, Stronghammer players like Autumn Jodoin are chugging raw eggs, shell and all! Sondra Elaina is polishing her boots with bacon grease! That, my friends, is the smell of impending victory! They've emerged from their Hollow Mine ready to prove that a little grit and grime beats prayers and polish every single time!\n\nSo grab your grog, place your bets with anyone who isn't Yarp, and settle in! The pitch is ready, the players are hungry, and the Trollball is practically humming with the promise of glorious violence! It's the righteous versus the rugged, the sacred versus the strong! This is going to be one for the ages! Let's get ready to TROLLBALLLLL! üí•",
    postGame:
      "### What a Game, Folks! A Defensive Duel to the End!\n\nAnd that's the final whistle, ladies and demons! A hard-fought, bone-crunching slugfest here at the Aegis Field has come to a close, and it's the visiting team who leaves with their heads held high! Your final score: **The Wyrmwood Stronghammers: 1, The Haven Lights: 0**! A shutout victory on enemy turf! You absolutely love to see it!\n\n### First Half Fury!\n\nThe first half was a masterclass in chaos! The Lights came out swinging, with Coward Tarton grabbing the ball early, but a fumbled pass set the tone for their offense all night. The first real statement was made by Haven's Marlane Lounge, who sent Rebane Kendy to the sidelines with a nasty shot from their Main-gauche! That's the beautiful game right there!\n\nBut the Stronghammers answered right back! A fantastic block by Cornela Piscatelli turned the tables, and the brawl was on! We saw bodies hit the floor left and right! Ultun Barthelemy took out Riffle Heyde with his Partisan! Godart Urissa sent Wieren Ivar packing with a Cestus! It was a beautiful, rotating door of pain, and the healers, Hamburger Marthe and Riffle Harrington, were working harder than Sir Garon Ironrock at a door convention!\n\nWe even had a spectacular double-knockout, as Odelia Abbott's whip and Tybi Reo's mace connected simultaneously, sending both warriors to the dirt! A perfect symphony of destruction! Not to be outdone, Cornela Piscatelli and Farand Keil decided to take a nap together after a vicious exchange. This is what Trollball is all about, folks!\n\nThen came the moment that decided it all. After a wild scramble and a teammate-on-teammate KO that was truly something to behold, Sabian Gleason made a powerful run, pushing deep into Haven territory. The ball found its way to Calvinna Isador, who dodged a block from Shiroma Salim and plunged into the end zone for a TOUCHDOWN! scored 1 point for The Wyrmwood Stronghammers! An absolutely stunning play that put the Stronghammers on the board!\n\n### Halftime Lull\n\nThe teams took a much-needed break to stitch up their wounds and plot their next moves. All KO'd players were returned to the field, fresh and ready for more glorious combat. You could feel the tension in the air, thick enough to cut with a Kriegsmesser.\n\n### Second Half Slugfest\n\nThe second half kicked off with even more violence! We had TWO double-KOs right out of the gate, as players from both sides decided to take each other out of the equation. The aggression was palpable! The Lights knew they had to score, and Dickenson Beker tried to lead the charge, but was stuffed by a brilliant block from Odelia Abbott.\n\nThe star of the second half, however, was Sondra Elaina for the Stronghammers! She scooped up the loose ball and made a magnificent run, tearing through the Haven defense like Cyfnerth through a buffet line. She looked for a pass, but the Lights' defense, for all their offensive failings, managed to hold her up. She was eventually blocked, and Haven took over.\n\nBut what did the Lights do with their chance? Riffle Heyde heaved a pass to Tybi Reo... who promptly fumbled it! Oh, the agony! Dropping the ball at a crucial moment like that is a mistake not even Sir Artorias could talk his way out of. That pristine 'Hallowed Ground' must be mighty slippery!\n\nIn a stunning display of d√©j√† vu, Sondra Elaina picked up the loose ball *again* and made the *exact same run*, breaking through the line and deep into Haven territory! It was poetry in motion! But alas, she was blocked once more, and the ball was loose on the field as the final whistle blew.\n\n### A Stronghammer Statement!\n\nAnd so, the Wyrmwood Stronghammers secure a magnificent 1-0 victory! They came into the home of the pious, weathered the storm, and walked away with the win, all thanks to that single, beautiful touchdown in the first half. The Haven Lights fought hard, but their offense just couldn't find a rhythm, fumbling away their best chances. Maybe they should spend less time chewing on roots and more time practicing catching the ball!\n\nWhat a night! What a game! Until next time, this has been Nok the Corrupter, reminding you that a broken bone is just a souvenir from a game well played! Goodnight, everybody! üòà",
