    preGame:
      "Hello, Trollball fanatics, and welcome to another glorious Tuesday Night Trollball! This is your favorite fiend, Nok the Corrupter, broadcasting live from the delightfully chaotic Unruly Yard in New Monteforte! The air is thick with the smell of cheap ale and impending violence, just the way I like it! üèüÔ∏è\n\nTonight, we've got a real barn-burner for you as the hometown heroes, The New Monteforte Chaos Creatures, take on the visiting stalwarts, The Kerlauger Runeguard! Both of these teams fall under the watchful eye of the White Ravens, so you know this is going to be a family squabble of the best kind‚Äîthe kind with spiked gauntlets and battle axes! Maybe Dame Terra Monteforte taught them a few tricks for rearranging the dirt... with their opponents' faces!\n\nDown on the field, the players are getting ready in their own special ways. For the Runeguard, I see Lashondra Niehaus getting a good, solid punch to the shoulder to wake her up, while Vivia Namara is slapping her own face after spitting in her hand! Now that's how you prepare for battle! You won't see Sir Artorias doing that before he goes off to bother some poor, misunderstood monster.\n\nAnd for the hometown Chaos Creatures, Alben Diantha is plunging his hands into ice-cold water‚Äîperfect for keeping a cool head when you're caving in someone else's! And Placido Kora is over there telling a joke to the Trollball itself! Let's hope it's a killer joke, folks, because we are just moments away from the opening whistle! Get ready for the mayhem!",
    postGame:
      "WHAT A GAME, FOLKS! WHAT A GAME! If that didn't get your blood pumping, you might want to check if you still have any! Your ol' pal Nok is still buzzing from that finish! An overtime thriller that went right down to the wire!\n\n### Final Score:\n*   **The Kerlauger Runeguard: 3**\n*   **The New Monteforte Chaos Creatures: 2**\n\nThe visiting Runeguard steals one in the Unruly Yard! The home crowd is absolutely furious, and it is BEAUTIFUL! üí•\n\nThis whole contest was a see-saw of glorious brutality from the second half onward! We saw bodies hitting the floor immediately, with Lorilee Aldred sending Raouf Dragone to the healers with a sharp greeting from their Katar. Both teams fought tooth and nail, trading possession like a hot rock, but neither could find the basket early on.\n\nThen, out of nowhere, Fogel Raynold of the Chaos Creatures gets his hands on the ball in Center Field, winds up, and lets it fly! It's good! A TWO-POINT SHOT that sends the hometown crowd into a frenzy! You could feel the unstable scaffolding shake from here!\n\nBut hold on to your helmets, because the Runeguard had an answer! On the very next possession, Vivia Namara scoops up the ball, takes aim from the same spot, and LAUNCHES IT! BINGO! Another two-pointer! We were all tied up, and the tension was thicker than mud in a bog!\n\nBoth teams scrapped for an advantage, trading blows and bruises. Johnna Beetner was a whirlwind with her Scimitar, dropping Chaos Creatures left and right. But neither side could break the deadlock. The whistle blew, and that beautiful word echoed across the yard: OVERTIME!\n\nAnd what an overtime it was! This wasn't just Trollball; this was a glorious, choreographed brawl! We saw more mutual knockouts than I've seen all season! Shepperd Trefler and Wolbrom Ariella took each other down in a symphony of destruction! Lashondra Niehaus and Mouldon Earl traded blows and both ended up napping on the turf! You love to see it!\n\nPossession was a fleeting dream as the ball was fumbled, dropped, and stolen again and again. It looked like neither team would ever score. It seemed this perfect display of violence might never end, a testament to the Everwar itself!\n\nBut then, the moment arrived. Amidst the chaos, the Runeguard's own Johnna Beetner‚Äîwho had been an absolute menace all night‚Äîgot her hands on the Trollball. She tucked it under her arm and charged for the goal line!\n\nPlacido Kora of the Chaos Creatures made a valiant effort to stop her, but Beetner would not be denied! She slipped past the block and dove into the end zone! TOUCHDOWN! THE KERLAUGER RUNEGUARD WINS IT AT THE DEATH!\n\nAn absolutely stunning finish to an incredible game of Trollball. My congratulations to the Runeguard for a hard-fought victory, and my thanks to both teams for putting on a spectacular show of pure, unadulterated carnage! Until next time, this is Nok the Corrupter, signing off! Now, let's see if this crowd riot is as good as the game was!",
