    preGame:
      "## TUESDAY NIGHT TROLLBALL IS ON THE AIR! üéôÔ∏è\n\nHello again, you beautiful brutes and belligerent beasts! This is your favorite fiend, Nok the Corrupter, coming to you live from the gilded stands of The Guilder's Field! The air here in New Prosperity is thick with the smell of gold and ozone, and I can tell you the crowd is absolutely electric! The bankers in their velvet boxes look a little nervous‚Äîthey should be! We're not here to sign ledgers, we're here to see ledgers balanced in BLOOD!\n\nTonight, we've got a real clash of philosophies for you! In one corner, we have the hometown heroes, The New Prosperity Profits! A team that understands the value of a well-placed spear and a hostile takeover. I've seen Yoshi Cathy getting ready by eating a raw onion, layer by layer, without shedding a tear! Now that's the kind of intestinal fortitude you need to win! And Boleslaw Heathcote is over there huffing the smoke from burning parchment‚Äîa ritual after my own heart!\n\nAnd in the other corner, visiting from the oh-so-sanctimonious woods of Hafting, it's The Greenwatch! I'm sure their patron, Sir Randy, polished his fancy bow just for the occasion. They've got some interesting characters, I'll give them that. I saw Verne Methuselah rubbing the Trollball in their armpits for grip‚Äîa classic technique! But then you've got Madea Mensch, tying his own bootlaces together and hopping to the line. An adventurer, ladies and gentlemen! Let's hope his fighting is better than his coordination!\n\nThe whistle is about to blow, folks! Will the Profits' aggressive portfolio of pain pay dividends? Or will The Greenwatch's natural approach bear fruit? One thing's for sure: it's going to be a glorious, bone-crunching spectacle! Stick around, you don't want to miss a single knockout!",
    postGame:
      "## WHAT A FINISH! WHAT A GAME! üí•\n\nBy my blackened, beating heart, what a game we just witnessed, folks! If you love back-and-forth brutality, last-second heroics, and sheer, unadulterated chaos, then you got your money's worth tonight! The Guilder's Field is in an uproar as the hometown New Prosperity Profits snatch victory from the jaws of The Greenwatch in overtime!\n\n### A Second Half Slugfest\n\nNow, the first half must have been a real barn-burner, with The Greenwatch managing to squeak out two points somewhere in the carnage, but the action we saw after halftime was a masterclass in mayhem! The Profits came out of the break looking to make a statement, and Pellikka Concettina did just that, sending Rese Halpern to the healer's tent with a lovely poke from his spear! \n\nBut The Greenwatch answered right back! Troy Jorgan brought that Kirkhammer down on Boleslaw Heathcote, dropping the ball carrier and sending a message! This half was not going to be easy!\n\n### The Body Count Rises\n\nAnd what a beautiful mess it became! We had a double knockout, a sight I will never get tired of, as Herriott Dhiren and Yoshi Cathy took each other out of the action in a spectacular clash of steel! The healers were earning their pay, running back and forth like panicked goblins in a gold mine! Nariko Javed and Merissa Mathian were the busiest people in the stadium!\n\nThen came the play of the game! With bodies littering the field, the Profits' own Abramson Doxia scooped up the ball, found a sliver of space, and launched a perfect, glorious two-point shot right through the basket! The crowd went wild! That, my friends, is how you tie a game and seize the momentum! An absolutely stunning display of skill and power!\n\n### A Moment of True Trollball Spirit\n\nI have to give a special mention to a moment of pure, unadulterated Trollball. In the midst of the fray, Greenwatch's Rese Halpern somehow... and you can't make this up, folks... knocked *themself* out with their own club. I haven't seen a player go down with a self-inflicted injury that beautiful since Sir Artorias tried to impress a fey by wrestling a cactus! A truly unforgettable moment of athletic incompetence!\n\n### Overtime Thrills!\n\nThe battle raged on, with neither team giving an inch. The field was a blender of flailing limbs and dropped players, sending us into a sudden-death OVERTIME! The tension was so thick you could carve it with a Kriegsmesser!\n\nThe Profits came out hungry. Yoshi Cathy, the onion-eater, grabbed the ball and went on a tear, running through the Greenwatch defense like a man possessed! He shrugged off a block attempt and dove headfirst into the endzone for the winning touchdown! \n\n### The Final Word\n\nAnd that's your ballgame, folks! The final score, after a nail-biting overtime period, is **The New Prosperity Profits 3, The Greenwatch 2**! \n\nLet the celebration begin in the streets of New Prosperity! A hard-fought, well-deserved victory for the home team, built on grit, violence, and a couple of spectacular scoring plays from Abramson Doxia and Yoshi Cathy!\n\nThat's all the time we have for Tuesday Night Trollball! Until next time, this is Nok the Corrupter, reminding you to always aim for the kneecaps! Good night, Osterra!",
