    preGame:
      "Hellooooooo Trollball fanatics and welcome back to TUESDAY NIGHT TROLLBALL! This is your favorite demonic announcer, Nok the Corrupter, coming to you live with a matchup that's sure to be a real barn-burner! üèüÔ∏èüî•\n\nTonight, we have a clash of titans as the visiting Starlight Bazaar Bizarres step onto the treacherous turf of the Oread's Summit Tamers! The Bizarres, hailing from the ever-chaotic Prismatic Pavilion, are used to a bit of razzle-dazzle, what with their home field's 'Troupe Distractions' and 'Unstable Footing'. They're a flashy bunch, with players like Kristin Kronfeld getting ready by having a teammate punch her square in the shoulder! Now that's how you get your head in the game! And let's not forget Gagliano Tallbott, who warms up by telling the Trollball itself a terrible joke. You gotta love the showmanship!\n\nBut they're facing a tough, tough home team in the Oread's Summit Tamers! These warriors play in the High-Pass Pitch, where the air is thin and a sudden blizzard can change the game in a heartbeat! This isn't some friendly circus performance like you'd get from Kython's troupe; this is hard-nosed, high-altitude Trollball! The Tamers are primed for battle, with rituals that could make Sir Tanos himself tremble. Alwyn Wandy whispers a secret fear to the Trollball before the game begins! Chilling! And you've got Odericus Juxon, who gets ready by slapping their own helmet until their ears ring! You can feel the intensity from here, folks!\n\nWill the Bizarres' flair and festival energy overcome the sheer grit of the mountain-dwelling Tamers? Or will the home team prove that thin air and a strong arm are all you need for victory? Forget whatever political nonsense is happening in the Guild of the Black Sky, because THIS is the only drama that matters tonight! Get ready for a symphony of destruction, folks, because the first whistle is about to blow!",
    postGame:
      "WHAT A GAME, FOLKS! WHAT A GAME! An absolute masterclass in violence and strategy from whistle to whistle! The Oread's Summit Tamers have defended their home turf, taking down the Starlight Bazaar Bizarres with a final score of 4 to 2! An incredible display of high-altitude dominance!\n\nThe action started immediately! The Bizarres' Milo Nelie scooped up the ball and, without a moment's hesitation, knocked Swamy Ahasuerus clear out of play with a beautiful swing of their Military Fork! That's how you start a Trollball game! But the glory was short-lived as Nelie fumbled a pass, leading to a mad scramble for the ball!\n\nKristin Kronfeld recovered for the Bizarres and made a powerful run deep into Tamer territory. It looked like an early score was in the cards, but WAIT! Alwyn Wandy of the Tamers came up with a MONSTROUS block, stripping the ball and taking possession! What a reversal of fortune!\n\nWandy didn't waste a second. With the home crowd roaring, they launched the Trollball from the 2-point zone... AND IT'S GOOD! Two points for the Oread's Summit Tamers! The High-Pass Pitch erupts! What a beautiful, beautiful shot!\n\nThe Tamers were just getting started! After another fumble by the Bizarres, who should recover the ball but Alwyn Wandy AGAIN! This player was simply on fire! While Wandy controlled the ball, we saw some glorious carnage unfold. Clippard Burr's Lance sent Aggri Cookie to the sidelines, and then we had a spectacular double knockout between Dric Trilley and Quintessa Austine! This is the kind of beautiful brutality that makes Trollball the greatest sport in Osterra!\n\nCapitalizing on the chaos, the Tamers moved the ball with precision. A clean pass from Wandy found Kass Fogel in scoring position, and Fogel wasted no time, sinking ANOTHER 2-point shot! Just like that, the Tamers were up 4-to-nothing as the first half came to a close! The Bizarres tried to make a late push with Willa Lois, but the Tamer defense held strong!\n\nAfter a much-needed halftime break to stitch everyone back together, the second half began with an absolute explosion of violence! It was a whirlwind of steel and bone as players from both sides were sent flying! Swamy Ahasuerus knocked out Melesa Zelten, only to be knocked out by Kristin Kronfeld! We had double KOs, triple KOs, healers on both sides working harder than Dame Terra trying to find a prophet to kidnap! It was magnificent!\n\nAmidst the beautiful mayhem, the Starlight Bazaar Bizarres found a spark! After a blocked run and a turnover, Gagliano Tallbott got their hands on the Trollball. With a clear look at the goal, Tallbott fired a perfect shot, scoring 2 points for the visitors! The Bizarres were on the board! The comeback was on!\n\nBut the Tamers' defense stiffened. They weathered the storm of the Bizarres' desperate attacks, with Zadoc Wyatan and Clippard Burr making key blocks and shutting down running lanes. The fighting was fierce right to the end, with another stunning double KO between Willa Lois and Kass Fogel keeping the healers busy.\n\nThe final minutes saw the Tamers controlling the ball, fending off the last, desperate attempts from the Bizarres. A final fumbled pass was recovered by Kristin Kronfeld, but it was too little, too late! The whistle blew, and the home team, The Oread's Summit Tamers, stood victorious!\n\nA hard-fought victory for the Tamers, who used their first-half momentum and rugged defense to seal the deal. A valiant effort from the Bizarres, who showed incredible heart in their second-half comeback attempt. It was a game filled with everything we love: incredible scoring, bone-crunching hits, and non-stop action! Until next time, this is Nok the Corrupter, signing off! What a night!",
